===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|lepen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hlēapan}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hlaupaną}} (compare {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|ljeppe|lang=fy}} ‘to jump’, Dutch {{term|lopen|lang=nl}} ‘to run; to walk’, German {{term|laufen|lang=de}} ‘to run’, Danish {{term|løbe|lang=en}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} (compare Lithuanian {{term|šlùbti|lang=lt}} ‘to become lame’, {{term|klùbti|lang=lt}} ‘to stumble’).

